items.title: Strengthening Our Core: Welcoming Karyne Levy as VentureBeat’s New Managing Editor
items.summary: Karyne Levy is joining VentureBeat as our new Managing Editor . She will be the central hub of the entire content operation . Her experience at Protocol, NerdWallet, Business Insider, CNET, and TechCrunch is a highlight reel of veteran tech journalism . She has a proven track record of managing people, running newsrooms, and interfacing with all parts of a business .

items.title: The beginning of the end of the transformer era? Neuro-symbolic AI startup AUI announces new funding at $750M valuation
items.summary: Augmented Intelligence Inc (AUI) has raised $20 million in a bridge SAFE round at a $750 million valuation cap . AUI relies on a fusion of the transformer tech and a newer technology called "neuro-symbolic AI . The round, completed in under a week, comes amid heightened interest in deterministic conversational AI and precedes a larger raise now in advanced stages .

items.title: Moving past speculation: How deterministic CPUs deliver predictable AI performance
items.summary: Modern CPUs have relied on speculative execution to keep pipelines full . But this architectural shift came at a cost: Wasted energy when predictions failed, increased complexity and vulnerabilities such as Spectre and Meltdown . This new deterministic approach may represent the first major architectural challenge to speculation since it became the standard . Early analysis suggests scalability that rivals Google’s TPU cores while maintaining significantly lower cost and power requirements .

items.title: Large reasoning models almost certainly can think
items.summary: There has been a lot of hullabaloo about the idea that large reasoning models (LRM) are unable to think . This is mostly due to a research article published by Apple . Apple argues that LRMs must not be able to think; instead, they just perform pattern-matching . This alone does not mean that LRM can think — just that we cannot be sure they don’t .

items.title: New tools in Google AI Studio to explore, debug and share logs
items.summary: Google AI Studio logo on a plain black background . Google's AI Studio is based on the company's AI lab's AI studio . Google AI studio is based in New York City, New York, and has been in existence since 2008 . Google has been working with AI Studio on a variety of AI-related topics . The company is now working with Google to develop a new AI studio called AI Studio in the US .

items.title: Why IT leaders should pay attention to Canva’s ‘imagination era’ strategy
items.summary: Canva hopes to position itself at the center of this shift with a sweeping new suite of tools . The company’s new Creative Operating System (COS) integrates AI across every layer of content creation . Users can tag @Canva to get copy suggestions and smart edits; or, they can highlight an image and direct the AI assistant to modify it or generate variants .

items.title: Meta researchers open the LLM black box to repair flawed AI reasoning
items.summary: Researchers at Meta FAIR and the University of Edinburgh have developed a new technique that can predict the correctness of a large language model's (LLM) reasoning and even intervene to fix its mistakes . The technique could help solve one of the great challenges of AI: Ensuring a model’s reasoning is faithful and correct .
